<subSubSection lastPageId="4" lastPageNumber="105" pageId="3" pageNumber="104" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1436,2009,2034]" lastBlockId="4.[151,1437,151,861]" lastPageId="4" lastPageNumber="105" pageId="3" pageNumber="104">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,273,2009,2034]" pageId="3" pageNumber="104">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Anterior dorsum pale yellow with brown areas; two pairs of narrow, irregular longitudinal brown stripes on mediolateral portions. Crown with three broad yellow stripes; pair of anteromedian diagonal brown arches connected medially. Pronotum with four yellow maculae, one elongate mediolateral pair and one lateral pair. Mesonotum with median yellow longitudinal stripe. Forewing red with brown veins; clavus with brown area and yellow elongate maculae between claval veins; corium with area of discal cells brown with yellow maculae; posterior portion of costal area with yellow maculae; apex dark. Face yellow with brown marks. Frons with pair of narrow, dorsomedian longitudinal brown stripes; brown inverted V-shaped median mark; lateral portions with narrow longitudinal brown stripe, slightly sinuous. Clypeus with large, dorsal brown macula. Male pygofer with short, tapered process on inner ventroapical margin. Paraphyses very similar to those of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Signoret" baseAuthorityYear="1855" box="[1160,1315,404,428]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Apogonalia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="105" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="blanchardi">
<emphasis box="[1160,1315,404,428]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="105">A. blanchardi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Aedeagal shaft with ventral paired processes. Female sternite VII (
<figureCitation box="[802,885,439,464]" captionStart="FIGURES 16 – 28" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1871,1894]" captionTargetBox="[230,1370,185,1860]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[216,1370,185,1860]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 16 – 28. (16 – 19) Apogonalia dampfi Young, 1977, female: 16, face; 17, sternite VIII, dorsal view; 18, valvulae I, basal portion, ventral view; 19, valvula II, apical portion, lateral view. (20 – 22) A. fractinota (Fowler, 1899), female: 20, sternite VII, ventral view; 21, sternite VIII, dorsal view; 22, valvula II, teeth on median portion, lateral view. (23 – 28) A. fraterna Young, 1977, female: 23, dorsal habitus; 24, left forewing, lateral view; 25, sternite VII, ventral view; 26, sternite VIII, dorsal view; 27, valvulae I, basal portion, ventral view; 28, valvula II, apical portion, lateral view. Scale bars in mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1035590/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="105">Fig. 20</figureCitation>
) with posterior margin broadly convex. Sternite VIII (
<figureCitation box="[214,296,476,501]" captionStart="FIGURES 16 – 28" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1871,1894]" captionTargetBox="[230,1370,185,1860]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[216,1370,185,1860]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 16 – 28. (16 – 19) Apogonalia dampfi Young, 1977, female: 16, face; 17, sternite VIII, dorsal view; 18, valvulae I, basal portion, ventral view; 19, valvula II, apical portion, lateral view. (20 – 22) A. fractinota (Fowler, 1899), female: 20, sternite VII, ventral view; 21, sternite VIII, dorsal view; 22, valvula II, teeth on median portion, lateral view. (23 – 28) A. fraterna Young, 1977, female: 23, dorsal habitus; 24, left forewing, lateral view; 25, sternite VII, ventral view; 26, sternite VIII, dorsal view; 27, valvulae I, basal portion, ventral view; 28, valvula II, apical portion, lateral view. Scale bars in mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1035590/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="105">Fig. 21</figureCitation>
) with large, subtrapezoidal sclerotized plate, slightly bilobate anteriorly and with pair of anterolateral projections.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,151,861]" box="[199,597,548,573]" pageId="4" pageNumber="105">
Female length. 
<quantity box="[372,507,548,573]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="9.149999999999999" metricValueMax="9.6" metricValueMin="8.7" pageId="4" pageNumber="105" unit="mm" value="9.149999999999999" valueMax="9.6" valueMin="8.7">8.7–9.6 mm</quantity>
(n = 2).
</paragraph>
