<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="105" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,151,861]" pageId="4" pageNumber="105">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,593,583,608]" pageId="4" pageNumber="105">Description of female genitalia.</emphasis>
Sternite VII (
<figureCitation box="[771,859,583,608]" captionStart="FIGURES 16 – 28" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1871,1894]" captionTargetBox="[230,1370,185,1860]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[216,1370,185,1860]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 16 – 28. (16 – 19) Apogonalia dampfi Young, 1977, female: 16, face; 17, sternite VIII, dorsal view; 18, valvulae I, basal portion, ventral view; 19, valvula II, apical portion, lateral view. (20 – 22) A. fractinota (Fowler, 1899), female: 20, sternite VII, ventral view; 21, sternite VIII, dorsal view; 22, valvula II, teeth on median portion, lateral view. (23 – 28) A. fraterna Young, 1977, female: 23, dorsal habitus; 24, left forewing, lateral view; 25, sternite VII, ventral view; 26, sternite VIII, dorsal view; 27, valvulae I, basal portion, ventral view; 28, valvula II, apical portion, lateral view. Scale bars in mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1035590/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="105">Fig. 20</figureCitation>
) slightly produced posteriorly; posterior margin irregular, broadly convex, with median trapezoidal emargination. Sternite VIII (
<figureCitation box="[1043,1125,620,645]" captionStart="FIGURES 16 – 28" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1871,1894]" captionTargetBox="[230,1370,185,1860]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[216,1370,185,1860]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 16 – 28. (16 – 19) Apogonalia dampfi Young, 1977, female: 16, face; 17, sternite VIII, dorsal view; 18, valvulae I, basal portion, ventral view; 19, valvula II, apical portion, lateral view. (20 – 22) A. fractinota (Fowler, 1899), female: 20, sternite VII, ventral view; 21, sternite VIII, dorsal view; 22, valvula II, teeth on median portion, lateral view. (23 – 28) A. fraterna Young, 1977, female: 23, dorsal habitus; 24, left forewing, lateral view; 25, sternite VII, ventral view; 26, sternite VIII, dorsal view; 27, valvulae I, basal portion, ventral view; 28, valvula II, apical portion, lateral view. Scale bars in mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1035590/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="105">Fig. 21</figureCitation>
), in dorsal view, with large, subtrapezoidal sclerotized plate; anterior margin of plate slightly bilobate, pair of narrow anterolateral projections; posterior margin truncate. Pygofer similar to that of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Signoret" baseAuthorityYear="1855" box="[769,927,692,716]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Apogonalia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="105" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="blanchardi">
<emphasis box="[769,927,692,716]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="105">A. blanchardi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Valvula I similar to that of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Signoret" baseAuthorityYear="1855" box="[1272,1429,692,716]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Apogonalia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="105" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="blanchardi">
<emphasis box="[1272,1429,692,716]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="105">A. blanchardi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Valvula II similar to that of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Signoret" baseAuthorityYear="1855" box="[472,627,728,752]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Apogonalia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="105" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="blanchardi">
<emphasis box="[472,627,728,752]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="105">A. blanchardi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; teeth spaced from one another about one time teeth length on median portion of blade (
<figureCitation box="[345,429,764,789]" captionStart="FIGURES 16 – 28" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1871,1894]" captionTargetBox="[230,1370,185,1860]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[216,1370,185,1860]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 16 – 28. (16 – 19) Apogonalia dampfi Young, 1977, female: 16, face; 17, sternite VIII, dorsal view; 18, valvulae I, basal portion, ventral view; 19, valvula II, apical portion, lateral view. (20 – 22) A. fractinota (Fowler, 1899), female: 20, sternite VII, ventral view; 21, sternite VIII, dorsal view; 22, valvula II, teeth on median portion, lateral view. (23 – 28) A. fraterna Young, 1977, female: 23, dorsal habitus; 24, left forewing, lateral view; 25, sternite VII, ventral view; 26, sternite VIII, dorsal view; 27, valvulae I, basal portion, ventral view; 28, valvula II, apical portion, lateral view. Scale bars in mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1035590/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="105">Fig. 22</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
